  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Human Resource Assistant",
  "description": "<p>We are a construction company that is currently engaged in multiple projects across the country, and we require a passionate member to join our team to better manage the human resources/ finance of the company and ensure that everything goes well.</p>\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>· One will be required to document down the various information/ details of the employees in an orderly manner.</li>\n  <li>· Keep a clear record of human resource information/ data to be fetched when needed.</li>\n  <li>· Be able to submit/ renew/ cancel work permits on MOM websites.</li>\n  <li>· Be able to communicate with MOM regarding employee’s issues.</li>\n  <li>· Process/ submit various government required documents/ claims.</li>\n  <li>· Be able to communicate with the workers regarding various issues.</li>\n  <li>· Partake &amp; be familiar in the company’s management process.</li>\n  <li>· In charge of employee’s training related matters.</li>\n  <li>· In charge of employee’s insurance processes.</li>\n  <li>· In charge of documenting company’s financial matters.</li>\n  <li>· Assist the company regarding construction project costing.</li>\n  <li>· Communicate with the agents regarding foreign workers employment.</li>\n  <li>· Other duties assigned by the manager from time to time.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>· One must have a Diploma/ Degree or equivalent qualification.</li>\n  <li>· One must be profound in the use of <strong>Microsoft Office software (e.g.: Excel)</strong></li>\n  <li>· One must be able to understand/ Speak/ write<strong> English in a native manner.</strong></li>\n  <li>· It is best if one has a previous experience in being a human resource</li>\n  <li>· One must<strong> be willing to travel to the construction sites when needed</strong> to deal with the on-site matters.</li>\n  <li>· Have an ‘<strong>on-time</strong>’&amp; positive attitude for work.</li>\n</ul>",
